		<title>17School at Carrowdore</title>
		<content> The children 60 years ago did not have
 books and pencils and pens the way we 
 do instead they used a slate and a    
 slate pencil.  This was difficult to  
 work on and very tiring. The teacher  
 wrote everyhting on the blackboard and
 then the children copied it out.      
 Handwriting was done in a copy book   
 with a push pen and ink.  The chidlren
 were not allowed to have one blot on  
 their page.  If they did they had to  
 start all over again.                 
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
